---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
const base = '/tradfi-onchain';
---

<Layout title="HK Regulation">
  <article class="max-w-3xl mx-auto px-6 pt-24 pb-24">
    <p class="text-cyan-400 text-sm font-medium tracking-wider uppercase mb-4">
      <span class="lang-en">Hong Kong Regulation</span><span class="lang-zh">香港監管</span>
    </p>
    <h1 class="text-4xl md:text-5xl font-bold text-white leading-tight mb-8">
      <span class="lang-en">HK Regulatory Landscape</span><span class="lang-zh">HK 監管現況</span>
    </h1>

    <div class="prose prose-invert prose-zinc max-w-none text-zinc-400 text-[15px] leading-relaxed space-y-6">

      <p>
        <span class="lang-en">Hong Kong is positioning itself as Asia's regulated crypto hub — more open retail access than Singapore, a clearer legal framework than mainland China. As of early 2026, the regulatory stack includes 12 licensed virtual asset trading platforms (2 approved for retail), 7 banks pursuing tokenized deposits, a stablecoin ordinance effective since August 2025, SFC-approved staking, and family office tax concessions covering digital assets. Over 3,380 single-family offices operate in Hong Kong.</span>
        <span class="lang-zh">香港正在定位為亞洲受監管嘅加密中心 — 比新加坡更開放嘅零售准入，比大陸更清晰嘅法律框架。截至2026年初，監管體系包括12間持牌虛擬資產交易平台（2間批准零售）、7間銀行推進代幣化存款、自2025年8月起生效嘅穩定幣條例、SFC批准嘅質押，以及涵蓋數字資產嘅家族辦公室稅務優惠。超過3,380間單一家族辦公室在香港運營。</span>
      </p>

      <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-white mt-16 mb-6">
        <span class="lang-en">VATP Licensing</span><span class="lang-zh">VATP牌照</span>
      </h2>

      <p>
        <span class="lang-en">The Securities and Futures Commission oversees Virtual Asset Trading Platform licensing. As of February 2026, twelve platforms hold licenses. HashKey Exchange and OSL Digital Securities were the first, licensed in August 2023, and remain the only two approved for retail trading — limited to BTC and ETH. The remaining ten serve professional investors only. Licensed platforms must comply with AML/KYC requirements, maintain 98%+ client assets in cold storage, carry insurance coverage, and segregate client assets from proprietary holdings.</span>
        <span class="lang-zh">證券及期貨事務監察委員會監管虛擬資產交易平台牌照。截至2026年2月，12間平台持有牌照。HashKey Exchange同OSL Digital Securities係首批，於2023年8月獲牌，至今仍係僅有嘅兩間獲准零售交易嘅平台 — 限於BTC同ETH。其餘十間僅服務專業投資者。持牌平台必須遵守AML/KYC要求，將98%以上客戶資產存放在冷存儲，維持保險覆蓋，並將客戶資產同自有持倉分隔。</span>
      </p>

      <p>
        <span class="lang-en">Compared to Singapore, which broadly restricts retail crypto trading, Hong Kong is clearly more open. Retail investors can trade BTC and ETH on regulated platforms with SFC-supervised custody. Other tokens remain professional-investor-only for now, but the retail perimeter is expected to expand over time.</span>
        <span class="lang-zh">相比新加坡全面限制零售加密交易，香港明顯更開放。零售投資者可以在受監管平台上交易BTC同ETH，享有SFC監管嘅託管。其他代幣目前仍限專業投資者，但零售範圍預計會隨時間擴大。</span>
      </p>

      <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-white mt-16 mb-6">Staking</h2>

      <p>
        <span class="lang-en">The SFC officially approved staking services for licensed VATPs in April 2025, jointly with the HKMA. Platforms must retain full custody control over staked assets — they cannot delegate to third-party validators without maintaining operational control. Clear risk disclosures covering slashing, lockup periods, and validator selection are required. Currently, ETH is the primary staking asset available through licensed platforms, offering roughly 3 to 4% APR. This is significant: it means licensed VATPs can now offer regulated crypto yield products to retail investors in Hong Kong — a first in Asia.</span>
        <span class="lang-zh">SFC於2025年4月聯同HKMA正式批准持牌VATP提供質押服務。平台必須保留對質押資產嘅完整託管控制 — 不可在未維持運營控制嘅情況下委託第三方驗證者。需要清晰嘅風險披露，涵蓋罰沒、鎖定期同驗證者選擇。目前ETH係通過持牌平台提供嘅主要質押資產，提供約3至4%年化收益。呢個意義重大：意味著持牌VATP現在可以向香港零售投資者提供受監管嘅加密收益產品 — 亞洲首創。</span>
      </p>

      <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-white mt-16 mb-6">
        <span class="lang-en">Stablecoin Ordinance</span><span class="lang-zh">穩定幣條例</span>
      </h2>

      <p>
        <span class="lang-en">The Stablecoins Ordinance was passed on May 21, 2025 and took effect on August 1, 2025. Regulated by the HKMA, it requires licensing for the issuance of fiat-referenced stablecoins in Hong Kong or HKD-pegged stablecoins anywhere. Issuers must maintain 100% reserve backing at all times with high-quality liquid assets, segregated from the issuer's own assets. Holders have an absolute right to redemption at par within one business day. Capital requirements include HK$25 million in paid-up share capital and HK$3 million in liquid capital.</span>
        <span class="lang-zh">穩定幣條例於2025年5月21日通過，2025年8月1日生效。由HKMA監管，要求在香港發行法幣掛鈎穩定幣或在任何地方發行港幣掛鈎穩定幣須持有牌照。發行人必須始終以高質量流動資產維持100%儲備支持，與發行人自有資產分隔。持有人有一個工作日內平價贖回嘅絕對權利。資本要求包括HK$2,500萬實繳股本同HK$300萬流動資金。</span>
      </p>

      <p>
        <span class="lang-en">HSBC, Standard Chartered, and OSL are among the applicants for stablecoin issuer licenses. If a G-SIB bank issues an HKD stablecoin under this framework, it would be among the world's first regulated stablecoins from a systemically important bank — dramatically lowering the barrier for institutional adoption of onchain settlement.</span>
        <span class="lang-zh">HSBC、渣打同OSL係穩定幣發行牌照嘅申請人之一。如果G-SIB銀行在此框架下發行HKD穩定幣，將係全球首批由系統重要性銀行發行嘅受監管穩定幣 — 大幅降低機構採用鏈上結算嘅障礙。</span>
      </p>

      <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-white mt-16 mb-6">
        <span class="lang-en">2026 New Legislation</span><span class="lang-zh">2026年新立法</span>
      </h2>

      <p>
        <span class="lang-en">Beyond VATPs and stablecoins, the government is preparing legislation for four additional categories of virtual asset service providers: VA Dealers (OTC dealing licensing), VA Custodians (custody service regulation), OTC Brokers (crypto brokerage licensing), and VA Advisors (investment advisory regulation, likely modeled on the existing SFC Type 4 license). Banks will not be exempt — those offering VA dealing or custody must register with the SFC. The consultation on extending oversight to VA advisers closed in January 2026.</span>
        <span class="lang-zh">除VATP同穩定幣外，政府正在為四個額外嘅虛擬資產服務提供商類別準備立法：VA交易商（場外交易牌照）、VA託管人（託管服務監管）、場外經紀（加密經紀牌照），同VA顧問（投資顧問監管，可能以現有SFC第4類牌照為藍本）。銀行不會獲豁免 — 提供VA交易或託管嘅銀行必須向SFC註冊。對擴大VA顧問監管嘅諮詢於2026年1月結束。</span>
      </p>

      <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-white mt-16 mb-6">
        <span class="lang-en">Family Office Tax Concession</span><span class="lang-zh">家族辦公室稅務優惠</span>
      </h2>

      <p>
        <span class="lang-en">From February 2026, digital assets are officially listed as qualifying investments under the family office tax concession regime. Family offices investing in digital assets through qualifying family-owned investment holding vehicles can enjoy profits tax exemption — the same treatment as equities and bonds. Previously, the tax treatment of crypto investments was ambiguous, requiring independent legal evaluation at significant cost. The policy change removes this barrier. Hong Kong has 3,380+ family offices; according to the HKIMR survey, 28% plan to increase digital asset allocations, while only 1% plan to decrease — the widest gap of any asset class. The government's target is to assist 220+ family offices to establish or expand in Hong Kong between 2026 and 2028.</span>
        <span class="lang-zh">自2026年2月起，數字資產正式列入家族辦公室稅務優惠制度下嘅合資格投資。通過合資格嘅家族所有投資控股載體投資數字資產嘅家族辦公室可享受利得稅豁免 — 與股票同債券相同嘅待遇。此前，加密投資嘅稅務處理係模糊嘅，需要高成本嘅獨立法律評估。政策變更消除咗呢個障礙。香港有3,380+間家族辦公室；根據HKIMR調查，28%計劃增加數字資產配置，僅1%計劃減少 — 所有資產類別中差距最大。政府目標係在2026至2028年間協助220+間家族辦公室在香港設立或擴展。</span>
      </p>

      <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-white mt-16 mb-6">e-HKD / CBDC</h2>

      <p>
        <span class="lang-en">The e-HKD Phase 2 pilot completed in October 2025. The HKMA has shelved retail CBDC for now, determining there is no near-term need. Instead, Hong Kong is pivoting to wholesale CBDC and bank-issued tokenized deposits — seven banks are actively pursuing tokenized deposit projects. This approach is closer to existing banking infrastructure than China's digital yuan model, with a lower adoption barrier. Hong Kong will not follow the government-issued retail CBDC path; the future is bank-issued tokenized deposits integrated with existing accounts.</span>
        <span class="lang-zh">e-HKD第2階段先導計劃於2025年10月完成。HKMA暫時擱置零售CBDC，判斷短期內無此需要。相反，香港轉向批發CBDC同銀行發行嘅代幣化存款 — 7間銀行正積極推進代幣化存款項目。相比中國數字人民幣模式，呢個方式更貼近現有銀行基礎設施，採用門檻更低。香港唔會走政府發行零售CBDC嘅路線；未來係銀行發行嘅代幣化存款，與現有賬戶整合。</span>
      </p>

      <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-white mt-16 mb-6">
        <span class="lang-en">Key Takeaway</span><span class="lang-zh">總結</span>
      </h2>

      <p>
        <span class="lang-en">The policy direction is consistent: build regulated infrastructure, encourage institutional adoption, and gradually expand retail access. VATP licensing, stablecoin ordinance, staking approval, family office tax concession — every move points in the same direction. More open than Singapore, clearer than mainland China. With VA dealers, custodians, OTC brokers, and advisors coming under regulation in 2026, the regulatory perimeter is expanding. For finance professionals in Hong Kong, the framework is no longer theoretical — it's operational, and it's growing.</span>
        <span class="lang-zh">政策方向係一致嘅：建立受監管基礎設施、鼓勵機構採用、逐步擴大零售准入。VATP牌照、穩定幣條例、質押批准、家族辦公室稅務優惠 — 每一步都指向同一方向。比新加坡更開放，比大陸更清晰。隨住VA交易商、託管人、場外經紀同顧問於2026年納入監管，監管範圍正在擴大。對香港金融從業者而言，呢個框架不再係理論 — 係運作中嘅，而且持續增長。</span>
      </p>
    </div>

    <!-- CTA -->
    <div class="mt-16 bg-gradient-to-r from-cyan-950/30 to-zinc-900/50 border border-cyan-900/30 rounded-xl p-8 flex flex-col md:flex-row items-center justify-between gap-6">
      <div>
        <h3 class="text-lg font-bold text-white mb-2">
          <span class="lang-en">See the full market landscape</span>
          <span class="lang-zh">睇完整市場動態</span>
        </h3>
        <p class="text-sm text-zinc-400">
          <span class="lang-en">Global institutional moves + Hong Kong developments.</span>
          <span class="lang-zh">全球機構動態 + 香港發展。</span>
        </p>
      </div>
      <div class="flex gap-4">
        <a href={`${base}/landscape`} class="px-5 py-2.5 bg-cyan-500 text-black text-sm font-medium rounded-lg hover:bg-cyan-400 transition-colors">
          <span class="lang-en">Market Landscape</span><span class="lang-zh">市場動態</span>
        </a>
        <a href={`${base}/products/polymarket`} class="px-5 py-2.5 border border-zinc-700 text-white text-sm rounded-lg hover:border-zinc-500 transition-colors">Polymarket</a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </article>
</Layout>
